OL,3,CFears 'outdated' divorce laws are
OL,4,Cbeing exploited by abusers
OL,6,FShe explains: "It takes so much of
OL,7,Fyour strength and pretty much
OL,8,Feverything you have to leave in the
OL,9,Ffirst place, and then you just have
OL,10,Fthis period of hanging over you that
OL,11,Fcontact has to resume at some point.
OL,13,F"There's no finality to it, you're
OL,14,Fjust stuck knowing that all those
OL,15,Ffeelings and all that pain and trauma
OL,16,Fare all going to come back to the
OL,17,Fforefront of your life, and again
OL,18,Fcouple of years down the line."
