OL,3,CFears 'outdated' divorce laws are
OL,4,Cbeing exploited by abusers
OL,6,FKate Wright, Chief Executive Officer
OL,7,Fof the domestic abuse charity FREEDA,
OL,8,Fsays: "It's clearly outdated. Divorce
OL,9,Fshouldn't be a second site for abuse,
OL,10,Fbut at the moment, Jersey laws do not
OL,11,Foffer protection to survivors from
OL,12,Feconomic, legal and emotional abuse,
OL,13,Flong after they've left their abuser.
OL,15,F"The impact on women is re-
OL,16,Ftraumatising; it prolongs the pain,
OL,17,Fand it allows the abuse to continue,
OL,18,Fsometimes for years.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/10
