OL,3,CFears 'outdated' divorce laws are
OL,4,Cbeing exploited by abusers
OL,6,FA decade ago, Jersey's States Assembly
OL,7,Fagreed in principle that the
OL,8,Flegislation should be updated.
OL,10,FFollowing this, a survey was carried
OL,11,Fout in 2019, which found that two-
OL,12,Fthirds of people were in favour of
OL,13,FJersey introducing 'no-fault' divorce.
OL,15,FITV News has heard from Deputy Mary Le
OL,16,FHegarat, Minister for Justice and Home
OL,17,FAffairs, who says draft legislation is
OL,18,Fbeing prepared that would, if
OL,19,Fapproved, replace Jersey's existing
OL,20,Fdivorce law.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G8/10
